cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DS 

This paper discusses the implementation of massive machine type communication (mMTC) in smart cities and the Internet of Everything, which involves wireless networks and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a new method for spatio-temporal modeling, which involves mathematical analysis and approximation techniques, indicating that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the integration of mMTC with cellular systems, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
